Milan Prosecutor Asks to Abandon Saras IPO Probe, Radiocor Says

-- B y   E l i s a   M a r t i n u z z i
-- 
2011-02-16T13:07:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/milan-prosecutor-asks-to-abandon-saras-ipo-probe-radiocor-says.html
A prosecutor in Milan asked a judge
to abandon a probe of alleged market manipulation and misleading
documents related to  Saras SpA ’s initial public offering in
2006, Radiocor news agency reported today.  Bankers from  JPMorgan Chase & Co .,  Morgan Stanley  and
Intesa Sanpaolo SpA’s Caboto unit had been probed. Officials for
the banks didn’t have an immediate comment.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Elisa Martinuzzi at 
 emartinuzzi@bloomberg.net  